<br>
I'm pretty happy with my resists and I still want to work up my AC a bit. My goal is to have an unbuffed AC of 1000 or so, without sacrificing too many of my other stats.  My resists are all above 80 (regardless of what Magelo says - I have some disease and poison augments I've added on to my gear)).<br>
<br>
I'm trying to keep in mind AC and +mana items as my next upgrades, since I see some clerics my season having 200 to 300 more mana than I do. It helps that I have Spellcasting Mastery 3 and Mental Clarity 1, but that can't really make up for extra mana *plus* those abilities. <br>
<br>
I'd also like to upgrade my current &quot;resist-only&quot; slots - namely, my mask and my rings. I will likely keep my rings, if I can ever find +wisdom augments for them. As for the face slot, it's something I've been looking to upgrade for a while. There is a comparable LDoN-earnable mask which I think I might end up getting, but I'm not sure yet.<br>
<br>
I also hope to do the clockwork talismans for my neck, so that's the other thing I really want to look at doing.<br>
<br>
