<br>
Your level 63 healing spell (can't remember what its called) is basically the replacement for complete heal. Although it chews up alot of mana for pop fights it is really really good. To make it most effective use a spell have IV item with the revernence buff to make its cast time quite fast. If you then have the improved healing aa and items the amount of hit points per second you can heal is amazing. This can come in very handy in pop named mob fights where the mob has a huge dps but very few hitpoints.... ie the fights dont last long enough for your FT to come into effect.<br>
<br>
For me personally the mana preservation focus effects are not that important as I generally group with a bard and chanter... thus mana regen isnt holding me back.... its just how many hitpoints I can heal per second that counts.<br>
<br>
Also don't forget that having lots of flowing thought isnt nescarrilly better than having a large mana pool. Lots of flowing thought is good for xp grinding, but for raiding and killing named mobs having a big mana pool is important. Just think how long it takes FT1 to regen 100 mana (10 minutes)... ie longer than the duration of most important battles..<br>
